us (COVID-19)|last=|first=|date=|website=|publisher=Northern Territory Government|language=en|url-status=live|archive-url=|archive-date=|access-date=2020-04-01}}</ref>{{Efn|On 27 March, NT Health added a case of a Queenslander diagnosed in Darwin yesterday to its tally, adjusting the total number of cases in the NT from 12 on 26 March to 13. <ref name=\"number of NT cases adjusted from 12 to 13\"/> <ref name=\"Queenslander diagnosed in the NT\"/> On 27 March, NT Health reported a Territorian being treated by NSW Health, but it did not count the case in its tally.<ref name=\"Territorian treated by NSW Health\"/> From 27 March onwards, the NT tally in this column includes the Territorian treated by NSW Health but not the Queenslander diagnosed in Darwin, so the total number of cases in the NT recorded in this column will be the same as that reported by NT Health.|name=|group=}} \n!{{nowrap|Total{{Efn|name=tn|group=}}}}\n!New<br/>cases\n!%<br/>growth\n!Deaths<br/>Nationally<ref>{{cite web|title=Coronavirus (COVID-19) current situation and case numbers |url=https://www.health.gov.au/news/health-alerts/novel-coronavirus-2019-ncov-health-alert/coronavirus-covid-19-current-situation-and-case-numbers |publisher=Department of Health |accessdate=31 March 2020}}</ref>\n|-\n|25 January\n|align=right|3\n|align=right|0\n|align=right|1\n|align=right|0\n|align=right|0\n|align=right|0\n|align=right|0\n|align=right|0\n|align=right|'''4'''\n|align=right|4\n|align=right|\n|0\n|-\n|27 January\n|align=right|4\n|align=right|0\n|align=right|1\n|align=right|0\n|align=right|0\n|align=right|0\n|align=right|0\n|align=right|0\n|align=right|'''6'''\n|align=right|2\n|align=right|\n|0\n|-\n|29 January\n|align=right|4\n|align=right|1\n|align=right|2\n|align=right|0\n|align=right|0\n|align=right|0\n|align=right|0\n|align=right|0\n|align=right|'''7'''\n|align=right|1\n|align=right|\n|0\n|-\n|30 January\n|align=right|4\n|align=right|2\n|align=right|3\n|align=right|0\n|align=right|0\n|align=right|0\n|a